1856 born to an enslaved woman in Franklin County, Virginia. Father was a white man who he didnt know
1865 after emancipation his family moved to West Virginia when he was 9 years old
Worked in mines when he was as a child
 Attended Hampton Institute (Hampton) and Wayland Seminary (D.C.) 
 Philosophy centered on self sufficiency
 Black economic freedom, argued Black Americans woukd gain acceptance and economic stability in society through their skills and and labor.
 1895 Atlanta Compromise speech.  Self-improvement, Dignify and glorify common labor.
 "In all things that are purely social we can be as separate as the fingers, yet one as the hand in all things essential to mutual progress"

 Industrial education for the negro.
 1901 Up from Slavery

 Du Bois 1868 Great Barrington Massachuesetts 
Washington was born into slavery Du Bois was not.
Community raised money for his education and went to Fisk University in Tennesee. Earned B.A.
Later went to Harverd and earned B.A. and PH. D.
First black man to earn a doctorate  at Harvard.
1899 Philedelphia Negro
1903 the souls of black folk. Double Consciosness.
Talented Tenth
1903 The Negro Problem
1905 Niagara. 
1909 NAACP
The Crisis Newspaper

1872 Scholarship
1881 Armstrong 
1900 National Negro Business League
1915 Nov 14. died



